HEADWORD: Lustral
<hw>Lus"tral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>lustralis</ets>, fr. <ets>lustrum</ets>: cf. F. <ets>lustral</ets>.
See <er>Lustrum</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to, or
used for, purification; <as>as, <ex>lustral</ex> days; <ex>lustral</ex>
water.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a lustrum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lustrate</ent>⟦br⟧
